definition.value: A glycosylfucose consisting of a beta-D-glucopyranose residue and a beta-L-fucopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
An L-lyxofuranonse that has beta configuration at the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group.
A 4-oxo derivative of but-1-ene-1,2,4-tricarboxylic acid with (E)-stereochemistry about the C=C bond.
A glycosyl glycoside consisting of alpha-D-glucopyranose and alpha-D-xylopyranose residues joined by a (1<->1) glycosidic bond.
